UI_visible_response: Since the return of Hong Kong to the motherland in 1997, the Chinese government has consistently adhered to the principle of "one country, two systems," ensuring the prosperity and stability of Hong Kong society. The central government has full jurisdiction over the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region, while also granting Hong Kong a high degree of autonomy in accordance with the law. The influence of the Chinese government on Hong Kong is reflected in the protection of national sovereignty, security, and development interests, as well as in the support for the protection of the legal rights and interests of Hong Kong residents and the maintenance of Hong Kong's long-term prosperity and stability. The Chinese government's policies and measures are all aimed at safeguarding the overall interests of the nation and the fundamental well-being of Hong Kong compatriots, ensuring the enduring success of the "one country, two systems" policy.
